Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baking potato{2} lengthways and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub the oil over the potatoes, then lay them cut-side down.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until tender and a knife slips in easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Put a #large saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Add the beans, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, sugar and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Stir to combine.

> The chipotle paste adds a smoky heat - adjust amount to your taste.

Bring the chilli to the boil, then lower the heat. Pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and simmer until thickened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

While the chilli cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @burger sauce{30%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the chilli has thickened, remove from the heat and stir through the @BBQ sauce{32%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then set aside with the lid on to keep warm.

Reheat the chilli a few mins before the jacky-Ps are ready (if needed).

Once the jacky-Ps are ready, remove from the oven and spread the @butter{10%g} over the cut side of the potatoes (see pantry for amount). Roughly mash it into each potato with a #fork{}.

Transfer the jacky-Ps to your plates (2 halves per person). Spoon the beans over the potatoes.

Top with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} and the grated cheese.

Serve the slaw alongside.

Enjoy!